sentence: Consumer products maker The Procter & Gamble Company ( PG ) on Friday caught some tepid commentary from analysts at Citigroup.
The firm maintained its "Buy" rating on PG but lowered its price target to $70.
That new target suggests a 12% upside to the stock's Thursday closing price of $62.29.
Citigroup also cut its earnings estimates for the company, citing its aggressive pricing strategy.
Shares of Procter & Gamble ( PG ) have a 3.61% dividend yield, based on last night's closing stock price of $62.29.
The stock has technical support in the $58-$60 price area.
If the shares can firm up, we see overhead resistance around the $64-$66 price levels.
